President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Kyle Hauptman, currently Senator Tom Cotton's advisor on economic policy, is nominated to be a Member of the National Credit Union Administration Board. Geeta Pasi, Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary for African Affairs at the Department of State, is nominated to be Ambassador to the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia. Cynthia Kierscht, Deputy Assistant Secretary in the State Department's Bureau of Western Hemisphere Affairs, is nominated to be Ambassador to the Islamic Republic of Mauritania. Each nominee brings significant experience and qualifications to their respective positions.